name: Stephanie Alcorn, ARNP
details: Stephanie Alcorn, ARNP joined The Iowa Clinic Urogynecology Department after years of experience in Women's Health. Over the years she’s practiced in an independent OB/GYN clinic as well as in high-risk maternity for a hospital.

graduate: University of Colorado at Colorado Springs
name: Tyler Aasen, DO
details: Dr. Tyler Aasen joined The Iowa Clinic in 2020. He chose The Iowa Clinic so he could be part of an organization that takes pride in providing high-quality patient care and one where physicians can be involved in leadership to make patient-centered decisions and policies

name: Naima Adeel, MD
specialty: Internal Medicine , Women's Center , Men's Center
details: Naima Adeel, MD has a mission to provide quality healthcare for her patients by utilizing a blend of excellent clinical knowledge, experience and effective communication. The Iowa Clinic’s goal of excellence in healthcare naturally aligned with her professional goals, which is why she brought her talent and experience here.

name: Lindsey Aeschliman, ARNP
details: Lindsey Aeschliman, ARNP joined The Iowa Clinic because of our multi-disciplinary approach to patient care. During her clinical rotation within the Internal Medicine Department, she was impressed by the teamwork among physicians and providers from other departments, who needed consultations for their patients.

graduate: Jordan University of Science and Technology, College of Medicine - Irbid, Jordan
name: Musab Alqasrawi, MD
details: Dr. Alqasrawi joined the Iowa Clinic in 2020 because he believes in the clinic’s philosophy and mission to provide the best care possible to patients. He also admires the clinic’s dedication to community health and quality care for the people of Iowa.

name: Bill Andrews, PA-C
details: Bill Andrews, PA-C joined The Iowa Clinic for the opportunity to work closely with multiple specialties all within one location. He brings 20 years of physician assistant experience in both rural communities and most recently at Mercy Medical Center. The Urgent Care Department offers unique challenges with a variety of patient cases on a daily basis, something Bill finds very fulfilling.

name: Jason Augustine, PT
details: Jason Augustine, PT, CSMT joined The Iowa Clinic with over 14 years experience. The start of his interest in physical therapy came in high school when he suffered a humeral fracture which required therapy as part of his recovery. This may be why he undoubtedly finds helping people overcome their injuries or ailments, the most rewarding part of being a physical therapist. Nobody asks for injuries, but unfortunately, they happen. They can also be a significant obstacle to overcome. To be able to help someone through that process and see their success makes his job so worth it.

name: Muhammad Awan, MD, FACC
details: Muhammad Awan, MD joined The Iowa Clinic after living in both the northeast and south during his fellowship and residency. But after experiencing “Iowa nice,” he and his wife decided Des Moines would be a great place to raise their family - among friendly and hardworking Iowans. The welcoming of the staff at The Iowa Clinic plus our academically oriented cardiovascular practice is what ultimately lead him here.
